ElementDescription: Which of these statements best describes the food eaten in your household: "enough of the kinds of food (I/we) want to eat; -enough, but not always the kinds of food (I/we) want; -sometimes not enough to eat; or, -often not enough to eat?
Notes: 1= Enough of the kinds of food we want to eat; 2= Enough but not always the kinds of food we want; 3= Sometimes not enough to eat; 4= Often not enough to eat

Notes: 0= Never; 1= Sometimes; 2= A lot; 999= Not Answered

Notes: 0= Never; 1= Sometimes; 2= A lot; 999= Not Answered

In the past 1 month, has your household experienced any of the following: Katika mwezi 1 uliopita, je, familia yako imepitia matukio yafuatayo: - You or any household member went to sleep at night hungry because there was not enough food.  Wewe au yeyote katika familia yako alilala na njaa usiku kwa sababu hakukuwa na chakula cha kutosha.
Notes: 2= Never. Kamwe; 3= Rarely (once or twice per month). Mara chache (mara moja au mbili kwa mwezi); 5= Often (more than 10 times in a month). Mara nyingi (zaidi ya mara 10 kwa mwezi); 6= Sometimes (3-10 times per month). Wakati fulani (mara 3 hadi 10 kwa mwezi)
